1
00:00:00,008 --> 00:00:10,008
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:09,352 --> 00:00:12,275
I think I know who did it.

3
00:00:12,659 --> 00:00:14,607
P’Oh-Lin… your friend.

4
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:16,152
Is Do still around?

5
00:00:16,411 --> 00:00:17,437
Show yourself.

6
00:00:18,112 --> 00:00:22,348
Direk, remember Do, the one who got killed?
He’s still lingering around.

7
00:00:23,136 --> 00:00:25,484
Do you think Mom is still around?

8
00:00:25,552 --> 00:00:27,555
Emma’s gone.

9
00:00:27,798 --> 00:00:29,309
Emma, stop nagging.

10
00:00:30,737 --> 00:00:35,305
I heard that kid next door who can talk to ghosts
I heard him talking to Emma, Direk.

11
00:00:35,417 --> 00:00:37,851
Emma’s still here, Direk.
Mom’s still here.

12
00:00:54,570 --> 00:00:55,510
What are you doing, sir?

13
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:56,910
You can’t go in.

14
00:00:57,650 --> 00:00:58,340
Why not?

15
00:00:58,730 --> 00:00:59,850
No entry without a pass.

16
00:00:59,910 --> 00:01:01,420
-I’m going up to see Direk.
-You can’t.

17
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,560
-No outsiders allowed.
-I’m going to see Direk.

18
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:04,870
Staff only.

19
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:06,300
You don’t know who I am?

20
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:07,370
No, I don’t.

21
00:01:20,980 --> 00:01:21,650
Little sperm.

22
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:23,880
What?

23
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:25,630
Hello, Direk.

24
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:27,350
Your security won’t let me in.

25
00:01:28,510 --> 00:01:29,870
What? Why?

26
00:01:30,870 --> 00:01:32,180
He says he doesn’t know me.

27
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,710
Is he new or something?

28
00:01:34,271 --> 00:01:35,814
Ok, hang on. I’ll handle it.

29
00:01:41,299 --> 00:01:44,524
Please check on this, my son can’t get into the company. He’s stuck outside.

30
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:32,450
Damn, what the hell are you wearing?

31
00:03:35,810 --> 00:03:37,240
Just grabbed whatever I could find.

32
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:40,710
If I were the guard, I wouldn’t let you in either.

33
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:47,610
Did you get any sleep?

34
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,360
I couldn’t sleep.

35
00:03:53,410 --> 00:03:54,400
About Emma?

36
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,910
Emma, stop nagging.

37
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,860
Since when did you become such a nag?

38
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:10,730
I’m not talking to you anymore.

39
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,450
Are you hallucinating or something?

40
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:36,080
Your mom can’t even speak Thai.

41
00:04:38,790 --> 00:04:39,220
Oh… right.

42
00:04:41,290 --> 00:04:41,860
Well…

43
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,040
I didn’t think about that.

44
00:04:46,610 --> 00:04:48,830
I was just shocked the name was the same.

45
00:04:49,370 --> 00:04:51,830
Emma’s such a common name anyway.

46
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:54,780
Who would think it’d be that much of a coincidence?

47
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:57,870
By the way—

48
00:04:59,080 --> 00:04:59,980
which Emma?

49
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:03,190
Since living in that condo,

50
00:05:03,830 --> 00:05:05,890
I’ve never heard of a ghost named Emma.

51
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:08,120
Do you really think this is about ghosts?

52
00:05:10,390 --> 00:05:12,050
That kid can talk to ghosts.

53
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,170
He can see and communicate with spirits.

54
00:05:16,070 --> 00:05:16,970
You don’t believe me, do you?

55
00:05:17,810 --> 00:05:19,290
Honestly, I wouldn’t either

56
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,090
if I hadn’t seen it myself.

57
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:24,700
What kind of crazy person talks to ghosts?

58
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,700
What are you even talking about?

59
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:28,490
Just listen first.

60
00:05:29,050 --> 00:05:31,190
The one who helped find Do’s killer

61
00:05:32,410 --> 00:05:33,160
it was him.

62
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:35,960
He talked to the ghost for us.

63
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:37,280
Shit.

64
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:41,100
You’re thinking of asking him to find Emma, right?

65
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:52,080
Wow, I’m really lucky today, got someone to drive me home.

66
00:05:52,570 --> 00:05:54,380
Maybe I should buy a lottery ticket.

67
00:05:58,790 --> 00:05:59,580
After you, Mr. President.

68
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:02,630
Direk!

69
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,720
Why’d you hit me? That hurts.

70
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,890
You’re asking for it.

71
00:06:25,390 --> 00:06:27,890
Since I’m sitting here, drive properly.

72
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,430
This isn’t a racetrack, got it?

73
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:32,090
Yes, sir.

74
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:40,460
Hey, you idiot—

75
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:49,260
Direk,

76
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:50,820
don’t forget to pay me for the ride.

77
00:06:51,120 --> 00:06:52,740
I didn’t drive you for free.

78
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:55,770
How much?

79
00:06:56,780 --> 00:06:57,410
Four hundred thousand.

80
00:06:58,980 --> 00:07:00,610
Go ask your dad for it.

81
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:02,510
I’m asking him right now.

82
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:09,030
Hey, I’m serious.

83
00:07:09,430 --> 00:07:11,360
I need it to fix my car, Direk.

84
00:07:11,830 --> 00:07:13,260
I’ll pay you back after the next race.

85
00:07:15,530 --> 00:07:16,700
No more racing.

86
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:19,350
Focus on your rotations. Focus on your studies.

87
00:07:19,620 --> 00:07:21,660
I’ve seen your grades—I’m seriously disappointed.

88
00:07:22,540 --> 00:07:23,270
What the hell?

89
00:07:25,580 --> 00:07:28,180
Look at your friends, especially Tonfah.

90
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:33,290
You’re the last person who deserves to be friends with him.

91
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:37,650
Wow.

92
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,970
No shame and you’re laughing?

93
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:45,120
-Ow!
-Then what’s the difference between me and Fah?

94
00:07:46,690 --> 00:07:49,610
That’s the dumbest question I’ve ever heard.

95
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,530
Seriously,

96
00:07:57,210 --> 00:07:58,350
can you handle med school?

97
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:01,400
Why would you ask that?

98
00:08:03,070 --> 00:08:05,180
Because I know you’re studying medicine for your mom.

99
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:10,350
You promised Emma you’d become a doctor to treat her.

100
00:08:11,010 --> 00:08:12,680
But now she’s gone.

101
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:18,490
If you want to change your mind now… no one’s gonna blame you.

102
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,060
Mom must be really disappointed then.

103
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,050
Emma’s not disappointed in you.

104
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,470
Same here.

105
00:08:38,970 --> 00:08:41,120
’Cause I never expected anything from you anyway.

106
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,830
You just got back from class and you're working again?

107
00:09:24,050 --> 00:09:25,940
Aren’t you pushing yourself too hard, Michael?

108
00:09:29,830 --> 00:09:31,600
I just wanna keep myself busy.

109
00:09:31,880 --> 00:09:33,280
So I don’t overthink.

110
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,490
I thought you said you don’t miss him anymore.

111
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:41,440
Khun Kim said he likes the cover we made.

112
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,910
Just need to tweak the lighting a bit.

113
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:46,500
Khun Kim’s easy to work with.

114
00:09:47,350 --> 00:09:49,720
He could totally become our regular client.

115
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:51,960
He’s hired us quite a few times already.

116
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:56,200
"Of course, dear client.

117
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:59,310
I’ll adjust the lighting a bit.

118
00:09:59,820 --> 00:10:01,460
and send it over ASAP."

119
00:10:05,370 --> 00:10:06,210
Open the door.

120
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,060
Open up.

121
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:11,060
Hey!

122
00:10:13,930 --> 00:10:14,650
Hey!

123
00:10:16,890 --> 00:10:17,600
Who’s Emma?

124
00:10:20,070 --> 00:10:21,660
-You heard that?
-Yeah.

125
00:10:26,050 --> 00:10:26,660
When?

126
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:28,640
Last night.

127
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:30,190
Shit.

128
00:10:31,080 --> 00:10:33,280
What? What do you mean “shit”?

129
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,180
It’s nothing.

130
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:37,030
Hey.

131
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,050
You still haven’t answered me.

132
00:10:39,310 --> 00:10:40,410
Who’s Emma?

133
00:10:42,180 --> 00:10:44,190
A wandering spirit or something?

134
00:10:54,700 --> 00:10:55,410
A friend.

135
00:10:56,940 --> 00:10:57,860
A friend or a ghost?

136
00:10:58,510 --> 00:10:59,250
Be honest.

137
00:11:01,230 --> 00:11:01,880
A friend.

138
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:11,480
An imaginary friend or what?

139
00:11:21,810 --> 00:11:22,320
Mm.

140
00:11:27,690 --> 00:11:30,460
What kind of guy is named Daotok? Sounds like a girl’s name.

141
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:32,630
I heard he can see ghosts too.

142
00:11:32,850 --> 00:11:35,310
Creepy. I’ve seen him talking to himself.

143
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,500
My mom said to stay away from him if possible.

144
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:39,850
Hi.

145
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:42,930
Can I sit with you?

146
00:11:43,980 --> 00:11:44,890
Sure.

147
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:46,590
What’s your name?

148
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:49,410
I’m Michael.

149
00:11:50,380 --> 00:11:51,320
Hi, Michael.

150
00:11:52,270 --> 00:11:53,610
Hi.

151
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:54,990
Emma.

152
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:04,170
Why Emma?

153
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:06,600
Emma Watson.

154
00:12:09,380 --> 00:12:11,140
I used to love Harry Potter as a kid.

155
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:17,930
Whatever.

156
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,410
Call them whatever the hell you want.

157
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,460
But can you use another name?

158
00:12:25,390 --> 00:12:26,500
Don’t use Emma.

159
00:12:28,660 --> 00:12:30,320
Emma is Emma.

160
00:12:31,270 --> 00:12:32,650
I’ve been using it for ages.

161
00:12:32,730 --> 00:12:34,100
I’m not changing it.

162
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:36,840
You—

163
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:43,270
Then...

164
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:46,880
Do me a favor.

165
00:12:47,990 --> 00:12:50,700
-No.
-Hey, what the hell is wrong with you?

166
00:12:50,860 --> 00:12:52,340
You keep slamming the door on me.

167
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,310
Are you gonna help me or not?

168
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,470
If you won’t,

169
00:12:58,380 --> 00:12:59,890
I’ll have North talk to you anyway.

170
00:13:01,970 --> 00:13:03,010
That’s cheating.

171
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:04,180
So what’s it gonna be?

172
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:07,160
Help with what?

173
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:11,170
Talk to Emma for me.

174
00:13:14,790 --> 00:13:16,490
Emma… my mom.

175
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:23,250
Talk to my mom for me.

176
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:31,790
In the bush—go, go!

177
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,540
Yeah, finish it!

178
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,230
Nice!

179
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:38,190
Nice, take the tower—nice!

180
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,700
That’s clean.

181
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:42,610
-Waiting for Jo?
-Yeah, P’.

182
00:13:43,660 --> 00:13:45,030
All done.

183
00:13:47,290 --> 00:13:47,710
Oh.

184
00:13:48,390 --> 00:13:49,430
What happened to you?

185
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,820
Are you the doctor or the patient?

186
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:53,430
Pick up your meds at counter two.

187
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:57,670
I’m not in the mood to mess with you today.

188
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:59,360
Don’t have the energy to argue either.

189
00:14:02,770 --> 00:14:03,670
Hey, North.

190
00:14:04,980 --> 00:14:05,960
Can I get your friend’s Line?

191
00:14:07,270 --> 00:14:09,440
Which friend? I’ve got tons of friends.

192
00:14:10,390 --> 00:14:11,390
The guy next door.

193
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:15,840
Oh, Daotok?

194
00:14:16,110 --> 00:14:16,650
Yeah.

195
00:14:18,870 --> 00:14:20,550
Are you trying to hit on my friend?

196
00:14:21,450 --> 00:14:22,480
Hell no.

197
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:23,680
What a relief.

198
00:14:24,330 --> 00:14:25,380
I thought you were hitting on him.

199
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,800
If you were,

200
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:30,020
I’d be the first to stop you no matter what.

201
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,610
No.

202
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:36,040
I just need his help with something.

203
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:37,240
It’s important.

204
00:14:38,620 --> 00:14:39,420
Important?

205
00:14:40,110 --> 00:14:42,120
He’s right next door. Why not ask him yourself?

206
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:43,440
Man...

207
00:14:44,630 --> 00:14:45,710
We keep missing each other.

208
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:47,410
When I’m in my room,

209
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:48,560
he’s not.

210
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:49,930
When he’s in,

211
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,630
I’ve gotta drag myself up early for rounds.

212
00:14:54,390 --> 00:14:54,850
Life...

213
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:57,820
Alright, I’ll send it to you.

214
00:14:59,040 --> 00:14:59,770
Hey, North.

215
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:01,990
Your friend...

216
00:15:02,910 --> 00:15:04,220
I don’t know if I should say this, but—

217
00:15:04,590 --> 00:15:05,220
he—

218
00:15:06,270 --> 00:15:07,020
What about him?

219
00:15:10,390 --> 00:15:11,850
He’s got an imaginary friend.

220
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:13,100
What?

221
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:14,580
Named Emma.

222
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,900
- Same name as my mom.
- Hey!

223
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:19,670
Emma.

224
00:15:20,580 --> 00:15:21,490
Emma.

225
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:26,310
- Emma!
- Asshole, how old are you? Still making fun of parents’ names, Nid?

226
00:15:26,750 --> 00:15:28,010
Hey, Nid is my mom.

227
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:29,530
Oh, really?

228
00:15:32,860 --> 00:15:35,280
So this “imaginary friend” thing—

229
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:36,860
is it real?

230
00:15:39,970 --> 00:15:40,990
I don’t know.

231
00:15:42,190 --> 00:15:43,900
But I’ve seen him talking like someone’s there.

232
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:46,460
Like really talking?

233
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,340
That’s creepy.

234
00:15:48,650 --> 00:15:50,660
Should he see a doctor?

235
00:15:50,890 --> 00:15:51,880
Is it dangerous?

236
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:53,760
A doctor?

237
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:55,440
No idea.

238
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:57,390
Maybe.

239
00:15:58,280 --> 00:15:58,710
Mm.

240
00:15:59,510 --> 00:16:00,300
I’ll talk to him.

241
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:02,590
Yeah, thanks.

242
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:05,850
Alright, I’m off.

243
00:16:06,530 --> 00:16:07,190
See you, P’.

244
00:16:07,430 --> 00:16:08,590
See you, Nid.

245
00:16:08,930 --> 00:16:09,950
Hey, that’s my mom!

246
00:16:11,210 --> 00:16:12,070
What’s with him?

247
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:37,620
Hey.

248
00:16:46,580 --> 00:16:48,310
Where’d you get my Line?

249
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:49,080
North.

250
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:56,270
Where?

251
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,250
Where?

252
00:16:58,950 --> 00:16:59,810
Where are you?

253
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:34,900
Mm.

254
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:46,360
Is she still around?

255
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:50,670
I don’t know.

256
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:51,950
What?

257
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:53,780
Well—

258
00:17:54,110 --> 00:17:55,640
that’s why I’m asking for your help.

259
00:18:01,910 --> 00:18:03,410
What if she’s not around anymore?

260
00:18:11,180 --> 00:18:12,370
Then I can finally move on.

261
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:24,270
Can you give me more details?

262
00:18:26,770 --> 00:18:27,420
Mm.

263
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:28,910
Go ahead.

264
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:32,822
What did she pass away from?

265
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:35,840
Cancer.

266
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,630
How long has it been?

267
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:47,350
Seven years.

268
00:18:48,110 --> 00:18:51,400
So… can you actually see if she’s with me?

269
00:19:00,250 --> 00:19:03,230
Let me finish my work first. I need to send this today.

270
00:19:15,900 --> 00:19:16,550
Yeah.

271
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:55,190
Hold on.

272
00:20:04,660 --> 00:20:06,160
Do you have a photo of your mom?

273
00:20:08,160 --> 00:20:08,620
Yeah.

274
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:21,720
So?

275
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:26,130
No.

276
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:29,670
What do you mean?

277
00:21:32,590 --> 00:21:33,420
There's no

278
00:21:35,230 --> 00:21:36,340
your mom.

279
00:21:42,270 --> 00:21:43,390
Are you sure?

280
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:45,980
Yeah.

281
00:21:48,070 --> 00:21:49,270
I checked everywhere.

282
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:13,390
If you wear that necklace, you won’t see ghosts?

283
00:22:13,630 --> 00:22:14,340
I still do.

284
00:22:14,620 --> 00:22:15,260
Then?

285
00:22:16,610 --> 00:22:17,900
So why wear it?

286
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:23,610
It only blocks weaker spirits.

287
00:22:24,130 --> 00:22:27,540
Some spirits—you need to take it off and focus to see them.

288
00:22:38,330 --> 00:22:39,300
Are you okay?

289
00:22:39,870 --> 00:22:41,360
You look pale as hell.

290
00:22:46,780 --> 00:22:47,240
Hey—

291
00:22:48,710 --> 00:22:50,530
What if Emma isn’t following me?

292
00:22:51,760 --> 00:22:54,590
She could be with my dad or somewhere else, right?

293
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:55,750
Right?

294
00:22:58,060 --> 00:23:00,860
It could be somewhere familiar—

295
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:03,890
or with someone she had a bond with.

296
00:23:05,020 --> 00:23:06,660
Anything’s possible.

297
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:13,950
Hey.

298
00:23:14,890 --> 00:23:16,400
Since you’ve helped me already,

299
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:18,710
can you help me a bit more?

300
00:23:20,860 --> 00:23:22,510
Can I say no?

301
00:23:23,220 --> 00:23:24,090
No.

302
00:23:32,070 --> 00:23:33,800
Has he texted you again?

303
00:23:43,470 --> 00:23:45,800
We’ll see each other soon. I miss you.

304
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:47,460
Why is he doing this?

305
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:49,340
Why would he come back?

306
00:23:49,750 --> 00:23:50,430
Right?

307
00:23:54,220 --> 00:23:55,820
What should we do, Emma?

308
00:23:57,150 --> 00:23:58,390
Should we just run away?

309
00:23:58,690 --> 00:23:59,480
Yeah.

310
00:23:59,690 --> 00:24:01,360
Run far away from him.

311
00:24:01,470 --> 00:24:02,840
How far is “far”?

312
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:28,070
Where are you going?

313
00:24:29,590 --> 00:24:30,700
I don’t know.

314
00:24:31,940 --> 00:24:33,070
That’s worrying.

315
00:24:33,710 --> 00:24:36,630
When Michael overthinks, you tend to do weird things.

316
00:24:39,980 --> 00:24:41,570
I’m not gonna do anything weird.

317
00:25:07,390 --> 00:25:09,400
Why’d you dye your hair that color?

318
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:13,920
Is it weird?

319
00:25:15,330 --> 00:25:15,870
Well…

320
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:17,810
Not really.

321
00:25:19,630 --> 00:25:21,690
Just… not used to it.

322
00:25:51,870 --> 00:25:52,250
Hey.

323
00:25:53,860 --> 00:25:55,000
Why are you so quiet?

324
00:25:56,620 --> 00:25:57,240
Why?

325
00:25:59,670 --> 00:26:01,680
Usually when people ride with me,

326
00:26:02,450 --> 00:26:03,800
they complain that I drive too fast.

327
00:26:05,010 --> 00:26:05,640
Mm.

328
00:26:06,340 --> 00:26:07,160
You do drive fast.

329
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:12,040
Aren’t you scared?

330
00:26:13,530 --> 00:26:13,960
No.

331
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:29,560
Hello there.

332
00:26:31,470 --> 00:26:32,120
Hello.

333
00:26:37,580 --> 00:26:39,290
Are you sure about this?

334
00:26:40,740 --> 00:26:41,290
Yeah.

335
00:26:42,830 --> 00:26:45,000
Do whatever you want.

336
00:26:46,740 --> 00:26:47,699
Make yourself at home.

337
00:27:02,670 --> 00:27:04,830
Thit, so?

338
00:27:06,030 --> 00:27:06,950
Yeah, wait a sec.

339
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:24,990
Emma liked this room.

340
00:27:25,835 --> 00:27:27,060
Even though she’s not here anymore,

341
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:30,912
we’ve kept everything of hers the same.

342
00:27:33,985 --> 00:27:36,201
What kind of husband are you? Your wife doesn’t even follow you.

343
00:27:36,709 --> 00:27:37,157
Hey.

344
00:27:38,539 --> 00:27:39,957
You…

345
00:27:40,696 --> 00:27:41,546
Direk.

346
00:28:05,370 --> 00:28:06,650
She’s not here either.

347
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:35,890
Hey.

348
00:28:36,290 --> 00:28:38,660
Are you sure this guy is reliable?

349
00:28:39,810 --> 00:28:40,340
Yeah, he is.

350
00:28:42,190 --> 00:28:44,810
He helped solve Do’s case last time.

351
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,350
But what if this time

352
00:28:49,790 --> 00:28:50,650
we don’t find her?

353
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:56,970
Then we’ll just have to let it go.

354
00:28:58,110 --> 00:28:58,550
Mm.

355
00:28:59,190 --> 00:28:59,630
Yeah.

356
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:02,440
Mm.

357
00:29:03,410 --> 00:29:04,560
We’ve come this far already.

358
00:29:09,110 --> 00:29:10,580
Why don’t we try going to her house?

359
00:29:14,710 --> 00:29:15,610
California, you mean?

360
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:16,570
Yeah.

361
00:29:17,410 --> 00:29:19,020
When Emma was with us,

362
00:29:19,420 --> 00:29:20,710
she mostly lived there.

363
00:29:20,950 --> 00:29:22,430
She only came to Thailand occasionally.

364
00:29:23,150 --> 00:29:25,750
If she’s still alive, she’d probably be there,

365
00:29:25,990 --> 00:29:26,820
not here.

366
00:29:32,290 --> 00:29:33,390
You mean…

367
00:29:36,420 --> 00:29:37,760
my mom might still be there?

368
00:30:24,910 --> 00:30:26,250
She likes it here.

369
00:30:27,070 --> 00:30:27,520
Huh?

370
00:30:34,380 --> 00:30:35,570
Your mom—

371
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,000
she likes it here, right?

372
00:30:41,500 --> 00:30:41,980
Yeah.

373
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:44,380
How do you know?

374
00:30:47,900 --> 00:30:49,030
I don’t know.

375
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:51,490
I can’t explain it.

376
00:30:54,010 --> 00:30:55,390
Maybe it’s just a feeling.

377
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:07,750
So only the feeling remains.

378
00:31:11,500 --> 00:31:12,610
But she’s gone.

379
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:21,360
She’s not here anymore.

380
00:31:30,870 --> 00:31:31,960
There’s one more place.

381
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:37,270
My mom’s house.

382
00:31:39,230 --> 00:31:39,820
Where?

383
00:31:42,870 --> 00:31:43,660
California.

384
00:31:53,350 --> 00:31:54,591
Let’s wait until the semester ends.

385
00:31:58,540 --> 00:31:59,490
So that’s a yes?

386
00:32:06,310 --> 00:32:06,920
Deal.

387
00:32:38,260 --> 00:32:38,860
What’s wrong?

388
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:45,590
Hey.

389
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:47,590
Hey—

390
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:50,420
You—

391
00:32:51,820 --> 00:32:52,561
What’s wrong with you?

392
00:33:02,130 --> 00:33:03,060
So what’s going on?

393
00:33:03,691 --> 00:33:04,798
You suddenly started crying.

394
00:33:10,066 --> 00:33:10,802
P’…

395
00:33:12,634 --> 00:33:12,988
Yeah?

396
00:33:17,130 --> 00:33:18,460
It’s because of you.

397
00:33:20,088 --> 00:33:20,961
What?

398
00:33:25,660 --> 00:33:26,620
I’m sorry.

399
00:33:28,074 --> 00:33:31,250
When I take off the necklace, I can’t really control my power.

400
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:35,450
Wait—

401
00:33:36,140 --> 00:33:37,670
What the hell do you mean?

402
00:33:40,100 --> 00:33:42,090
I accidentally read your feelings.

403
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:57,570
Who told you to mess with my feelings?

404
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:04,910
I'm sorry.

405
00:34:06,450 --> 00:34:07,680
I didn't mean to.

406
00:34:17,450 --> 00:34:18,700
Then why are you crying?

407
00:34:29,610 --> 00:34:30,060
What?

408
00:34:34,750 --> 00:34:37,120
Why are you such a sad person?

409
00:34:44,770 --> 00:34:46,450
Do I really look that sad?

410
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:03,630
But I'm not someone who cries easily.

411
00:35:10,810 --> 00:35:12,870
Are you stupid or what?

412
00:35:13,500 --> 00:35:14,810
Crying for someone else?

413
00:35:22,420 --> 00:35:22,870
What?

414
00:35:24,210 --> 00:35:25,791
You're looking at me like you're insulting me.

415
00:35:27,290 --> 00:35:27,980
Yeah.

416
00:35:29,110 --> 00:35:29,810
I am.

417
00:35:33,100 --> 00:35:33,750
Shit.

418
00:36:09,910 --> 00:36:10,420
P'.

419
00:36:13,080 --> 00:36:14,010
I'm sorry.

420
00:36:16,780 --> 00:36:18,680
For accidentally reading your feelings.

421
00:36:23,420 --> 00:36:23,930
Yeah.

422
00:36:25,390 --> 00:36:26,630
Whatever.

423
00:36:32,960 --> 00:36:33,810
Thanks, man.

424
00:36:34,550 --> 00:36:35,630
For helping with my mom.

425
00:36:56,349 --> 00:36:58,790
Hey, what's up with P'Thit hair?

426
00:36:59,327 --> 00:37:02,220
That's just how he is. He woke up late and didn’t fix his hair.

427
00:37:07,614 --> 00:37:09,230
I'll see you at the hospital.

428
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:12,680
Okay. I miss you.

429
00:37:13,910 --> 00:37:14,410
Hey.

430
00:37:15,110 --> 00:37:16,500
New hair?

431
00:37:16,830 --> 00:37:19,440
Damn, that looks cool as hell.

432
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:21,800
Where are Ter and Maew?

433
00:37:22,030 --> 00:37:23,310
Those two are studying all day.

434
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:24,390
I just found out,

435
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:27,030
vet and photo majors are insanely demanding.

436
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:28,460
Who can I even report this to?

437
00:37:28,770 --> 00:37:30,290
My friends are gone all day.

438
00:37:31,069 --> 00:37:33,160
But engineering’s probably just as tough, right?

439
00:37:38,350 --> 00:37:40,100
Hey, Daotok.

440
00:37:40,140 --> 00:37:41,220
I’ve got something to ask you.

441
00:37:41,540 --> 00:37:41,990
Yeah.

442
00:37:42,710 --> 00:37:44,080
About Emma.

443
00:37:51,090 --> 00:37:52,390
P'Arthit told me,

444
00:37:52,980 --> 00:37:54,390
but he didn’t mean any harm.

445
00:37:54,650 --> 00:37:56,550
I talked to him, and I think

446
00:37:56,850 --> 00:37:57,710
he’s worried about you.

447
00:37:58,580 --> 00:37:59,866
That’s why I had to talk to you.

448
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:02,290
North.

449
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:03,910
Hm?

450
00:38:05,420 --> 00:38:06,310
Aren’t you scared?

451
00:38:06,900 --> 00:38:07,570
Scared of what?

452
00:38:08,430 --> 00:38:09,720
Aren’t you scared of me?

453
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:12,120
What are you talking about?

454
00:38:16,140 --> 00:38:17,990
Emma’s been with me since I was a kid.

455
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:20,450
Hey, seriously?

456
00:38:21,750 --> 00:38:23,100
She didn’t disappear when you grew up?

457
00:38:25,060 --> 00:38:25,590
Whoa.

458
00:38:25,910 --> 00:38:26,350
So,

459
00:38:26,700 --> 00:38:27,910
what kind of person is Emma?

460
00:38:28,750 --> 00:38:30,100
She’s kind.

461
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,580
She understands everyone.

462
00:38:34,500 --> 00:38:37,700
I can talk to her about anything.

463
00:38:38,420 --> 00:38:39,945
Hey, you can talk to me about anything too.

464
00:38:43,370 --> 00:38:44,060
Yeah, yeah.

465
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:45,580
She's a good person. That's enough

466
00:38:46,410 --> 00:38:47,730
I’m just worried about you.

467
00:38:49,470 --> 00:38:50,980
Hey, I’ve got one more thing.

468
00:38:52,780 --> 00:38:53,700
About…

469
00:38:54,210 --> 00:38:54,840
P'Arthit.

470
00:38:56,230 --> 00:38:58,410
- Let’s not talk about him.
- Why?

471
00:38:59,370 --> 00:39:00,050
What’s going on?

472
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,280
- He made me cry.
- What?

473
00:39:06,630 --> 00:39:08,790
He made someone as numb as you cry?

474
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:15,310
Sorry, I didn’t mean to call you numb.

475
00:39:16,770 --> 00:39:17,720
Sometimes you just seem like it.

476
00:39:21,690 --> 00:39:23,550
Hey, talk to me first.

477
00:39:24,370 --> 00:39:26,050
- I’m not talking to North anymore.
- Hey.

478
00:39:26,710 --> 00:39:27,780
You’re really sulking at me?

479
00:39:28,660 --> 00:39:30,060
I already said sorry.

480
00:39:39,020 --> 00:39:39,780
Have you been waiting long?

481
00:39:41,160 --> 00:39:41,860
Not long.

482
00:39:42,660 --> 00:39:43,720
Just got back from club activities.

483
00:39:47,180 --> 00:39:48,600
I heard you made my friend cry.

484
00:39:50,490 --> 00:39:50,940
Huh?

485
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:52,670
What did you do to him?

486
00:39:53,580 --> 00:39:57,650
What the hell? My friend’s tough as hell, look at him now.

487
00:39:58,310 --> 00:39:59,700
You must’ve done something serious.

488
00:39:59,990 --> 00:40:01,070
Tell me right now, P'Thit.

489
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,690
Hey, hey—I didn’t do shit.

490
00:40:06,230 --> 00:40:07,020
What the hell?

491
00:40:08,140 --> 00:40:08,870
Yo, Jo, I’m heading out.

492
00:40:09,390 --> 00:40:10,610
-Hey.
-Yeah, see you.

493
00:40:10,900 --> 00:40:13,160
P'Thit, get back here and tell me now!

494
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:15,290
Hey! P’Thit! Thit!

495
00:40:15,340 --> 00:40:17,300
-Damn it.
-If you wanna know, go ask him yourself.

496
00:40:18,710 --> 00:40:19,300
Calm down.

497
00:40:40,470 --> 00:40:41,450
Shit.

498
00:40:41,710 --> 00:40:42,630
What the hell is this?

499
00:41:05,230 --> 00:41:06,590
Hello?

500
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,300
Yeah.

501
00:41:09,540 --> 00:41:10,270
Wanna play a game?

502
00:41:10,820 --> 00:41:12,830
-No.
-What the hell?

503
00:41:12,990 --> 00:41:14,590
Guess your junior don’t matter anymore, huh?

504
00:41:15,420 --> 00:41:16,790
I’ve got an early morning tomorrow.

505
00:41:17,790 --> 00:41:18,590
Your husband, huh?

506
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:20,070
Go to sleep.

507
00:41:21,220 --> 00:41:21,990
Yeah, right.

508
00:41:22,630 --> 00:41:24,800
He’s got an early ward shift with us tomorrow.

509
00:41:26,190 --> 00:41:28,760
I told you, you came later.

510
00:41:29,290 --> 00:41:31,490
You think you can cut into me and Jo?

511
00:41:32,410 --> 00:41:33,440
Not a chance.

512
00:41:35,130 --> 00:41:37,970
So I really am just the backup, huh?

513
00:41:39,070 --> 00:41:41,190
One day P'Jo’s gonna dump me, right?

514
00:41:41,560 --> 00:41:42,490
Damn you.

515
00:41:44,040 --> 00:41:44,970
Who are you talking to?

516
00:41:46,780 --> 00:41:49,800
I need to learn to be on my own.

517
00:41:50,810 --> 00:41:51,990
You’re so full of shit.

518
00:41:52,390 --> 00:41:53,350
Be on your own? What's that?

519
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:54,770
It' not gonna happen.

520
00:41:58,940 --> 00:42:00,660
This dumbass again.

521
00:42:05,210 --> 00:42:06,500
Jo, you idiot—

522
00:42:06,740 --> 00:42:08,730
The hell? You’re the idiot, Thit.

523
00:42:09,510 --> 00:42:10,630
How’d you hear that?

524
00:42:30,730 --> 00:42:32,740
-Hey, North.
-Yeah, P'?

525
00:42:32,950 --> 00:42:33,800
Let me ask you something.

526
00:42:34,810 --> 00:42:36,900
If someone cried for you,

527
00:42:39,460 --> 00:42:40,390
how would you feel?

528
00:42:41,390 --> 00:42:42,230
Who?

529
00:42:42,630 --> 00:42:44,440
Daotok?

530
00:42:46,950 --> 00:42:47,910
My friend.

531
00:42:48,750 --> 00:42:50,160
My friend.

532
00:42:50,970 --> 00:42:52,470
Your friend? Who?

533
00:42:54,540 --> 00:42:55,210
Daeng.

534
00:42:56,270 --> 00:42:56,750
Daeng.

535
00:42:57,380 --> 00:42:58,170
Daeng. His name’s Daeng.

536
00:42:58,450 --> 00:42:59,140
My friend’s name is Daeng.

537
00:42:59,980 --> 00:43:01,510
That fake name sounds stupid, P’.

538
00:43:02,370 --> 00:43:06,230
Then why cry for him? Why doesn’t he cry himself?

539
00:43:07,530 --> 00:43:10,040
How the hell would I know? I’m not Daeng.

540
00:43:10,380 --> 00:43:11,630
Then let me guess.

541
00:43:12,010 --> 00:43:16,060
Daeng’s the type who doesn’t like crying, keeps everything in.

542
00:43:16,370 --> 00:43:19,160
Never tells anyone, just bottles it up.

543
00:43:21,300 --> 00:43:23,131
What an idiot. Thinks that makes him cool or something?

544
00:43:23,560 --> 00:43:26,330
In the end, the one who gets hurt is you, dumbass.

545
00:43:26,660 --> 00:43:29,480
You’ve got people to talk to, yet you keep it all to yourself.

546
00:43:29,590 --> 00:43:31,150
Why act so tough?

547
00:43:32,830 --> 00:43:34,670
I feel bad for Daeng.

548
00:43:35,300 --> 00:43:36,470
What’s your problem?

549
00:43:37,920 --> 00:43:39,700
P'Jo asked me to tell you this.

550
00:43:40,990 --> 00:43:42,250
Jo, you idiot.

551
00:43:43,210 --> 00:43:45,590
-Tell him yourself. I’m not saying it.
-So?

552
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:48,510
Is this really about Daeng or someone else?

553
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:52,610
Daeng.

554
00:43:54,390 --> 00:43:55,600
He told me to say it.

555
00:43:57,180 --> 00:43:58,610
Oh.

556
00:43:59,530 --> 00:44:00,580
P'Jo.

557
00:44:01,240 --> 00:44:01,580
Hmm?

558
00:44:02,020 --> 00:44:02,620
P'Thit

559
00:44:02,950 --> 00:44:06,650
says, “I’m not telling you, dumbass.”

560
00:44:06,950 --> 00:44:08,840
That’s from Daeng.

561
00:44:09,420 --> 00:44:11,100
You’re so dead, asshole.

562
00:44:11,210 --> 00:44:13,590
- Oh, you mean Daeng?
- No, I mean you, Thit.

563
00:44:16,630 --> 00:44:17,360
Savage.

564
00:44:35,060 --> 00:44:35,790
Hey, son.

565
00:44:38,350 --> 00:44:39,740
Hello, Khun John.

566
00:44:40,910 --> 00:44:41,970
I missed you.

567
00:44:42,120 --> 00:44:43,270
You din't miss me, right?

568
00:44:43,920 --> 00:44:45,280
Of course I do.

569
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:47,100
I missed you and Dad the most.

570
00:44:47,340 --> 00:44:48,280
Missed you too.

571
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:50,840
Khun John,

572
00:44:51,520 --> 00:44:52,550
how was your trip?

573
00:44:54,770 --> 00:44:57,880
The outside is so nice.

574
00:44:58,020 --> 00:44:58,410
Um.

575
00:44:58,610 --> 00:45:01,620
But the rent so cheap, right.

576
00:45:01,700 --> 00:45:02,160
Yes.

577
00:45:02,390 --> 00:45:06,420
I thought it’d be an abandoned condo.

578
00:45:06,550 --> 00:45:07,930
Yes, I thought that too.

579
00:45:09,470 --> 00:45:12,490
This is the only place around here that allows pets.

580
00:45:12,620 --> 00:45:13,710
I see.

581
00:45:13,750 --> 00:45:14,450
That's why.

582
00:45:17,580 --> 00:45:19,190
Let’s go inside.

583
00:45:19,480 --> 00:45:20,390
Sounds good.

584
00:45:45,380 --> 00:45:47,430
Mr.John gained about one kilo.

585
00:45:49,230 --> 00:45:52,310
Which one of you made him gain weight?

586
00:45:52,860 --> 00:45:54,650
Oh, it was definitely Phai.

587
00:45:55,300 --> 00:45:56,570
Excuse me?

588
00:45:57,630 --> 00:46:00,090
Just kidding.

589
00:46:31,940 --> 00:46:33,140
How have you been?

590
00:46:35,430 --> 00:46:36,990
Khram’s coming back to Thailand.

591
00:46:41,290 --> 00:46:42,630
Do you still miss him?

592
00:46:48,010 --> 00:46:49,120
Not at all.

593
00:46:51,070 --> 00:46:52,700
I don’t miss him.

594
00:46:53,790 --> 00:46:55,770
I don’t want to go back either.

595
00:46:58,110 --> 00:46:59,960
But every time I think of him,

596
00:47:02,230 --> 00:47:03,680
it still hurts.

597
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:16,310
I’ll be in Chicago for three years.

598
00:47:17,140 --> 00:47:18,920
Aren’t you really coming to see me off?

599
00:47:20,180 --> 00:47:20,820
No.

600
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:22,950
Dao.

601
00:47:24,700 --> 00:47:25,710
Are you okay?

602
00:47:27,650 --> 00:47:29,220
Are you mad at me for having to be apart?

603
00:47:30,810 --> 00:47:31,830
But it’s okay.

604
00:47:32,140 --> 00:47:34,140
I’ll come back to see you often, Dao.

605
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:35,170
Okay?

606
00:47:42,390 --> 00:47:43,370
From now on,

607
00:47:44,450 --> 00:47:45,730
you don’t have to come back anymore.

608
00:47:49,280 --> 00:47:49,910
Dao.

609
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:56,140
I’ve been trying to look pass it all this time,

610
00:47:57,140 --> 00:47:59,230
because I believed people make mistakes.

611
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:03,750
But sneaking around with my friend?

612
00:48:04,910 --> 00:48:05,950
Isn’t that going too far?

613
00:48:12,580 --> 00:48:14,950
Dao, I can explain this.

614
00:48:21,050 --> 00:48:22,840
Since you’re going abroad anyway,

615
00:48:24,050 --> 00:48:25,840
please get out of my life too.

616
00:48:28,150 --> 00:48:29,210
Let’s not see each other again.

617
00:48:39,640 --> 00:48:41,250
It still hurts.

618
00:48:46,310 --> 00:48:47,880
But the reason it still lingers

619
00:48:48,430 --> 00:48:50,200
is there something left unresolved?

620
00:48:51,380 --> 00:48:54,210
When you broke up, you never really cleared things up.

621
00:48:55,530 --> 00:48:56,750
There must be

622
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:59,170
a lot left in your heart.

623
00:48:59,500 --> 00:49:01,950
About yourself and about him.

624
00:49:03,970 --> 00:49:06,070
Do you want me to go talk to Kram, Dad?

625
00:49:07,350 --> 00:49:08,520
Just a suggestion.

626
00:49:10,590 --> 00:49:11,980
Whichever path you choose,

627
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:14,730
I’ll support you.

628
00:49:16,240 --> 00:49:20,040
But running away for years like this hasn’t helped at all.

629
00:49:21,540 --> 00:49:24,310
It’s better to be honest and talk about why it happened,

630
00:49:24,380 --> 00:49:29,220
what caused it, and what’s still unresolved between you.

631
00:49:29,820 --> 00:49:31,350
So you can finally settle it.

632
00:49:34,570 --> 00:49:35,820
And I also think

633
00:49:36,150 --> 00:49:38,110
he couldn’t take care of you.

634
00:49:41,010 --> 00:49:42,250
So I want you to talk it out,

635
00:49:42,710 --> 00:49:44,210
so you can move on,

636
00:49:44,760 --> 00:49:46,650
and not end up back here again.

637
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:50,020
You understand what I mean, right?

638
00:49:58,270 --> 00:49:59,010
Okay.

639
00:50:01,450 --> 00:50:02,800
If he comes back,

640
00:50:04,280 --> 00:50:06,250
I’ll find a chance to talk to him.

641
00:50:08,310 --> 00:50:09,310
That’s good.

642
00:50:09,730 --> 00:50:11,020
And don’t go alone.

643
00:50:11,330 --> 00:50:12,710
Bring someone with you.

644
00:50:14,790 --> 00:50:15,980
Someone.

645
00:50:26,900 --> 00:50:27,420
Hey.

646
00:50:28,360 --> 00:50:29,900
What can I do for you?

647
00:50:31,760 --> 00:50:33,530
Dad, who’s that?

648
00:50:41,030 --> 00:50:41,780
What is it?

649
00:50:44,870 --> 00:50:45,350
Uh…

650
00:50:46,150 --> 00:50:48,390
Just wanted to ask when you’re free.

651
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:51,870
Whenever you are.

652
00:50:52,830 --> 00:50:55,140
I’ve only got a few exams left before break.

653
00:50:56,790 --> 00:50:57,830
Mm.

654
00:50:58,660 --> 00:50:59,250
Okay.

655
00:50:59,540 --> 00:51:01,390
I won’t bother you then.

656
00:51:17,790 --> 00:51:18,640
Dad?

657
00:51:22,570 --> 00:51:24,110
“Daddy” not meaning father?

658
00:51:26,530 --> 00:51:27,940
Damn, this kid’s got guts.

659
00:51:29,400 --> 00:51:30,350
Not bad.

660
00:51:37,240 --> 00:51:38,880
A friend?

661
00:51:39,930 --> 00:51:41,920
My neighbor.

662
00:51:42,530 --> 00:51:43,810
Knocking that loudly?

663
00:51:44,320 --> 00:51:45,960
No manners at all.

664
00:51:47,630 --> 00:51:48,430
Exactly.

665
00:51:52,800 --> 00:51:53,910
Actually,

666
00:51:54,460 --> 00:51:56,390
I’m going to California

667
00:51:56,830 --> 00:51:58,570
during the break.

668
00:52:01,010 --> 00:52:02,070
On vacation?

669
00:52:03,580 --> 00:52:04,510
Not quite.

670
00:52:05,510 --> 00:52:07,220
I have something to take care of.

671
00:52:08,150 --> 00:52:09,040
Your friend?

672
00:52:11,670 --> 00:52:13,430
The guy who just knocked the door.

673
00:52:17,770 --> 00:52:18,870
Long story.

674
00:52:51,050 --> 00:52:52,230
Mr. John’s here.

675
00:52:53,160 --> 00:52:55,040
- So cute.
- I wanna play with him.

676
00:52:56,310 --> 00:52:57,190
You’re obsessed.

677
00:53:04,610 --> 00:53:05,170
Where are you going?

678
00:53:06,580 --> 00:53:07,260
Getting coffee.

679
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:11,000
On a motorcycle?

680
00:53:12,590 --> 00:53:12,920
Yeah.

681
00:53:20,690 --> 00:53:21,510
I’ll take you.

682
00:53:22,150 --> 00:53:22,760
It’s late.

683
00:53:27,950 --> 00:53:28,440
Come on.

684
00:53:52,280 --> 00:53:53,370
Aren’t you bringing work?

685
00:53:54,630 --> 00:53:56,060
I need to get back to Mr. John.

686
00:53:57,910 --> 00:53:59,250
The one in your room?

687
00:54:00,880 --> 00:54:02,330
Mr. John is a cat.

688
00:54:03,550 --> 00:54:03,940
Oh.

689
00:54:09,390 --> 00:54:12,650
It wasn’t easy clearing my schedule for California.

690
00:54:13,340 --> 00:54:15,180
I even got Direk to pay for my ticket.

691
00:54:16,440 --> 00:54:17,740
You’re not gonna ditch me, right?

692
00:54:24,870 --> 00:54:25,380
Hey.

693
00:54:25,930 --> 00:54:26,900
Why so quiet?

694
00:54:28,980 --> 00:54:30,540
In return for helping you,

695
00:54:31,300 --> 00:54:33,200
I’ve got a condition.

696
00:54:34,630 --> 00:54:35,770
What condition?

697
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:42,200
Help me deal with my ex.

698
00:54:42,520 --> 00:54:43,020
Huh?

699
00:54:46,180 --> 00:54:47,870
So what’s going on with your ex?

700
00:54:48,470 --> 00:54:49,770
Did he stop bothering you?

701
00:54:56,290 --> 00:54:58,660
Then let P’Arthit help you.

702
00:55:01,850 --> 00:55:02,980
What do you mean?

703
00:55:03,570 --> 00:55:06,180
Have P’Arthit deal with your ex for you.

704
00:55:07,750 --> 00:55:09,780
- Is that a good idea?
- It is.

705
00:55:10,560 --> 00:55:13,660
An ex like yours who keeps harassing you—

706
00:55:13,930 --> 00:55:16,330
-Kram.
-Kam? Who the hell’s named Kam?

707
00:55:17,180 --> 00:55:18,150
Kram.

708
00:55:18,400 --> 00:55:20,370
Yeah, that asshole Kram—

709
00:55:20,560 --> 00:55:22,120
he needs to deal with someone like my brother.

710
00:55:26,170 --> 00:55:26,710
Hey.

711
00:55:27,360 --> 00:55:28,680
Trust me.

712
00:55:28,770 --> 00:55:29,930
Let P’Thit help you.

713
00:55:31,238 --> 00:55:33,220
He already owes you one anyway.

714
00:55:34,110 --> 00:55:35,110
And besides,

715
00:55:35,360 --> 00:55:37,260
P’Thit isn’t useful for much,

716
00:55:37,510 --> 00:55:38,730
but this is one of them.

717
00:55:39,240 --> 00:55:40,340
He can be your guard dog.

718
00:55:41,650 --> 00:55:44,220
Honestly, I wanna help you too,

719
00:55:44,730 --> 00:55:48,350
but if you get back with your ex, I’ll look like an idiot.

720
00:55:48,850 --> 00:55:50,450
So I’ll send P’Arthit to bark in my place.

721
00:55:50,750 --> 00:55:51,700
Woof.

722
00:56:17,510 --> 00:56:18,390
My ex…

723
00:56:18,990 --> 00:56:19,780
Help me.

724
00:56:29,640 --> 00:56:30,510
Alright.

725
00:56:43,070 --> 00:56:43,640
Who is it?

726
00:56:44,540 --> 00:56:45,780
What’s your problem, asshole?

727
00:57:00,810 --> 00:57:01,860
So?

728
00:57:02,140 --> 00:57:07,250
If you miss someone,
does that mean you still love them?

729
00:57:07,450 --> 00:57:10,820
Dao, thanks for helping me.

730
00:57:10,860 --> 00:57:13,370
Don’t you ever think about opening your heart?

731
00:57:25,890 --> 00:57:28,320
If you’re still around, come see our son sometimes.
